lenders.name: Faye
lenders.occupational_info:
Web Design

The Internet has evolved very quickly and so has web design.  We have gone from coding websites by hand to what you see is what you get web 

editors that simplified it some to content management systems like WordPress, Joomla and custom systems that make for very robust and expandable 

websites.  Some are so easy to implement that a complete novice can use some of them.

You turn on the Television and you see commercials about these website builders and they say things like make it, publish it and get found as if 

it is that easy and to be frank with you, it is a sham to sell their system that makes them recurring monthly income.  Nothing wrong with that, 

but it is a little deceiving.

Is there a difference in a custom site and one I can do myself using one of these site builders?

The answer is a simple yes.  We cannot tell you how many times we have heard people say that they built a website but no one comes to it or that 

they do get some traffic from it but it doesn’t convert those visitors into actual clients or customers.

Most people focus on the look of the website…is it pretty…does it have flashing stuff on it.  While there is nothing wrong with having a 

beautiful website, it must also contain other elements that will help drive customer conversions and ultimately sales.

Creating a high converting website starts with first knowing who your customer is and what they want.  What are the questions they are asking?  

What are their needs and wants?  Are they predominately men or women?  Where do they hangout?  What income brackets are they in?  These are all 

questions that have to be answered in order to create a website that converts.

Websites and Search Engines

Once you have answered several questions and developed direction for the site, then it needs to be built in a search engine friendly way.  That 

used to be coding by hand in what is called HTML and CSS.  Now these have not gone away but they are used in a more powerful and advanced way.

Today, the choice of most web-designers are platforms like WordPress, Joomla, Drupal, Magento and many more.  WordPress, however, has surged 

ahead as a platform of choice due to the ease of development, SEO friendly coding and the ability to implement just about any design in to it 

and a full range of user-friendly extensions to expand it to whatever level you would like.

There are several design firms that have created their own content management systems and many of those a good as well.  Here at Reddoch Media 

Group, we can design and implement for several different platforms but WordPress is our platform of choice for the reasons mentioned above.  Our 

clients can easily manage their site if they want with a little training or we can do it for them.

Your website is your online retail space.  It is like having another store location.  With that in mind, you need to make sure that it is 

drawing attention, pulling potential customers in the door and pointing them to what they want and making it easy for them to buy it whether it 

is a product or a service.

Website Design and Content

Once your website is designed it then needs high quality content in not only text but video and audio as well.  Developing this content begins 

with keyword research that identifies just what your potential customers are looking for.  Then content is written and even turned into video or 

audio and placed on the site.  The keywords are woven into the content in a natural way.  When the search engines index that content, they have 

very complex algorithms that analyze the content and determine where it should come up in the search results.

The writing of content with proper use of keywords is called “on page optimization.”  This is a very critical part of the SEO process and is 

more than just writing something and hoping to be found.

At Reddoch Media Group, we don’t just design sites.  Our goal is to create a powerful conversion tool that improves your bottom line and gets 

you the exposure you desire.  If you don’t have content, we create it for you and work with you to help engage your potential customer in fresh 

and dynamic ways.

If you would like a website that can really make a difference in your business or for your personal brand, give us a call today.

lenders.name: jonah roll
lenders.occupational_info:
Jonah’s work is a combination of traditional oil painting techniques and mix media assemblage. Utilizing found wood and repurposed objects, often boat parts, he creates ships, sea creatures, and nautical images. 
 
 Jonah was born and raised on a 45-foot sailboat, The Flying Walrus, in Honolulu, Hawaii. At the age of 12, he moved to the Big Island, where the mythology and natural world of Hawaii saturated his formative mind. 
 In 1989, Roll received a Bachelor of Fine Arts in print-making from the Pacific Northwest College of Art in Portland, Oregon.

 Influenced by his watery beginnings, his love for boats and nautical lore Jonah’s work takes the viewer on a journey to surreal destinations, suffused  with imagery imbedded in an original and stylized reality, often peopled with characters that range from the grotesque to the majestic.

 He has created artworks for the public and many of his pieces are included in private collections. His work has been exhibited in Hawaii, Portland, Seattle, San Francisco, Santa Cruz, Washington D.C., and New York.
